Ver1.5
  - sleep-power-control: skip CPU freq clamp when on AC, with 30s AC poll while screen is off
  - new sleep-cpu-governor service: drops to `powersave` below 20% battery, restores `schedutil` at >=25% (with hysteresis)
  - add Makefile wrapping build/install/clean/status/logs targets

Ver1.4
  - drop usage of `pyinstaller` (services are now shell wrappers, not compiled binaries)
  - replace inotify simple with inotify
  - source files extracted to `src/` - no longer inlined as heredocs
  - no need to build package as `root`
  - translate Korean to English in error message 
  - improve documentation
  - fixed logging (now the print statements appear in journal)
  - add CHANGES file

Ver1.3
  - autodetect path to power key

Ver1.2
  - Add customization (`/etc/uconsole-sleep/config`)
  - Power saving CPU freq now follows a user-specified value, not available value.

Ver1.1
  - Add feature hold power key to trigger `KEY_POWER` (interactive power menu)

Ver1.0
  - Official keyboard firmware detection
  - Apply timeout poll for desktop sleep mode detection
  - Use the `detect` flag instead of `on` forcing LCD turned on.

Ver0.3
  - Emit WakeUp Event after turn on screen
  - Add DRM control to turn off screen (BL,LCD) (not blank)

Ver0.2 
  - initial release
